cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CY, cs.SD 

This paper deals with natural language processing and machine learning techniques for sentiment detection in code-switched text. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also involves techniques for data augmentation and transfer learning, which are common topics in machine learning and deep learning research, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely category. Additionally, the paper involves the use of automatic translations, which falls under the category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also involves the use of constituency parses, which falls under the category of cs.CY (Computational Geometry). Finally, the paper involves the use of hate speech detection, which falls under the category of cs.SD (Sound and Music Computing).
